---
const facts = [
  {
    n: 'The dose question',
    title: 'A standard dose may not be your dose',
    body: 'Too much can mean nausea and misery; too little can mean little progress. Your biology has its own response, and a generic ramp does not account for it.',
  },
  {
    n: 'The side-effect question',
    title: 'Some risks show up in your data first',
    body: 'Concerns like muscle loss and nutrient depletion can appear in your biomarkers before you feel them. Measuring first gives you and your clinician something concrete to watch.',
  },
  {
    n: 'The after question',
    title: 'What happens when you stop matters',
    body: 'How and when a course is adjusted is part of the plan, not an afterthought. Knowing your starting picture helps inform that conversation.',
  },
];
---

<section class="section section--tight problem">
  <div class="container narrow center">
    <h2 class="problem__title" data-reveal>
      GLP-1 can be powerful. Starting it blind is where people get nervous.
    </h2>
    <p class="lede" data-reveal style="--reveal-delay: 0.08s">
      The difference between a good experience and a hard one often comes down to
      information you do not have yet. There are three questions worth answering first.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="facts" data-stagger>
      {facts.map((f) => (
        <article class="fact">
          <p class="fact__n">{f.n}</p>
          <h3 class="fact__title">{f.title}</h3>
          <p class="prose fact__body">{f.body}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .problem__title { font-size: var(--step-2); margin: var(--sp-3) auto var(--sp-4); max-width: 24ch; }
  .facts {
    margin-top: var(--sp-7);
    display: grid; gap: var(--sp-4);
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
  }
  .fact {
    padding: var(--sp-5);
    border-top: 2px solid var(--jade);
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--surface) 0%, var(--ink) 130%);
    border-radius: 0 0 var(--radius) var(--radius);
  }
  .fact__n { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: var(--step--1); color: var(--jade); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.02em; }
  .fact__title { font-size: var(--step-1); margin: var(--sp-2) 0 var(--sp-3); }
  .fact__body { color: var(--muted); }
</style>
